00:13:40.887 --> 00:13:44.302
Um. yeah. I might just be
running a teeny bit late.

259
00:13:44.303 --> 00:13:45.929
But...

260
00:13:47.845 --> 00:13:49.970
Why's that?

261
00:13:53.095 --> 00:13:54.511
Oh.

262
00:13:54.512 --> 00:13:56.594
Yeah. No. he is... he is my...

263
00:13:56.595 --> 00:13:59.136
uh. my ex-husband.

264
00:14:06.470 --> 00:14:08.345
Okay. makes sense.

265
00:14:10.553 --> 00:14:12.303
Thanks. You. too.

266
00:14:15.220 --> 00:14:17.636
Well. that's a record.

267
00:14:17.637 --> 00:14:19.970
I got fired
before I started my job.

268
00:14:21.845 --> 00:14:23.386
'Cause of me?

269
00:14:23.387 --> 00:14:25.219
Hi.

270
00:14:25.220 --> 00:14:26.637
Hi.

271
00:14:27.595 --> 00:14:28.970
Everything okay?

272
00:14:33.136 --> 00:14:34.679
Yeah. it's fine.

273
00:14:36.553 --> 00:14:38.427
Fuck. it's the kids' school.

274
00:14:38.428 --> 00:14:40.219
Hello?

275
00:14:40.220 --> 00:14:42.302
Yeah.

276
00:14:42.303 --> 00:14:44.053
He did what?

277
00:14:45.470 --> 00:14:47.386
Sure. Yeah. I'll-I'll...

278
00:14:47.387 --> 00:14:48.469
I'll come right over.

279
00:14:48.470 --> 00:14:50.636
Soon as I can. Thanks.

280
00:14:50.637 --> 00:14:52.177
Trevor got in a fight.

281
00:14:52.178 --> 00:14:54.010
- Oh. my God. Is he okay?
- They didn't give any detail.

282
00:14:54.011 --> 00:14:55.678
They just told me to come
and pick him up.

283
00:14:55.679 --> 00:14:57.761
No. I'm going.

284
00:14:57.762 --> 00:14:59.344
Yeah. Helen.
the school called me.

285
00:14:59.345 --> 00:15:01.511
- Yes. because it was probably your fault.
- Please.

286
00:15:01.512 --> 00:15:03.594
That may be true. but it's
really important to me

287
00:15:03.595 --> 00:15:05.678
to get to him. to talk
to him. to explain.

288
00:15:05.679 --> 00:15:08.011
Well. that's not happening.

289
00:15:22.679 --> 00:15:25.095
I'm sorry about the job.

290
00:15:32.762 --> 00:15:35.720
I worked my ass off
for that job.

291
00:15:38.220 --> 00:15:40.511
I didn't go to Montauk
to plan my daughter's wedding

292
00:15:40.512 --> 00:15:41.678
to get that job.

293
00:15:41.679 --> 00:15:43.637
Do you know how painful
that was for me?

294
00:15:44.679 --> 00:15:46.552
But doesn't matter. really.

295
00:15:46.553 --> 00:15:47.761
'cause you know what?

296
00:15:47.762 --> 00:15:49.219
No matter how hard I work.

297
00:15:49.220 --> 00:15:52.177
you always manage to find a way
to fuck my shit up.

298
00:15:52.178 --> 00:15:54.636
- I said I was sorry.
- Well. if you want to apologize.

299
00:15:54.637 --> 00:15:57.219
why don't you start
with those women?

300
00:15:57.220 --> 00:16:00.469
How can I apologize. Helen.
when I didn't do anything?

301
00:16:00.470 --> 00:16:01.886
Oh. really?
So they're all lying?

302
00:16:01.887 --> 00:16:03.636
- Why would they do that?
- I don't know.

303
00:16:03.637 --> 00:16:05.177
That's what I'm trying
to figure out.

304
00:16:05.178 --> 00:16:06.929
Oh. so you didn't sleep
with the student teacher?

305
00:16:08.095 --> 00:16:10.135
It was... it was consensual.

306
00:16:10.136 --> 00:16:12.469
Oh. except you were her boss!

307
00:16:12.470 --> 00:16:15.844
So maybe it didn't feel
consensual to her.

308
00:16:15.845 --> 00:16:18.344
And what about Eden?

309
00:16:18.345 --> 00:16:21.511
She came to my room. uninvited.
and we made out for maybe

310
00:16:21.512 --> 00:16:22.636
fucking one minute.
That was it.

311
00:16:22.637 --> 00:16:24.344
But why did you let her in?

312
00:16:24.345 --> 00:16:26.260
Did you think maybe that
might have been a bad idea?

313
00:16:26.261 --> 00:16:28.678
- Because I was drunk.
- Well. whose fault is that?

314
00:16:28.679 --> 00:16:30.678
- Yours. actually! Yes.
- What?

315
00:16:30.679 --> 00:16:32.052
Earlier in the night.
we went out.

316
00:16:32.053 --> 00:16:33.302
As usual.
you were drinking like a fish.

317
00:16:33.303 --> 00:16:35.719
You got me shit-faced. That was
why I didn't kick her out

318
00:16:35.720 --> 00:16:36.719
- immediately!
- Are you seriously trying

319
00:16:36.720 --> 00:16:38.219
to turn this around on me?

320
00:16:38.220 --> 00:16:39.761
Your inability
to take responsibility

321
00:16:39.762 --> 00:16:41.678
for your actions
is pathological.

322
00:16:41.679 --> 00:16:44.052
- Oh. really? Really?!
- Yeah. Yeah.

323
00:16:44.053 --> 00:16:47.010
Well. maybe 'cause I'm so busy
taking responsibility for yours!

324
00:16:47.011 --> 00:16:49.679
Oh. my God. Fuck you!

325
00:16:57.720 --> 00:17:02.052
I've done time for a crime
I didn't commit already. Helen.

326
00:17:02.053 --> 00:17:04.220
I'm not doing it again.

327
00:17:15.095 --> 00:17:17.594
- Excuse me. What's going on?
- They're shutting down Sunset

328
00:17:17.595 --> 00:17:20.177
to help with evacuations
off the 405.

329
00:17:20.178 --> 00:17:21.594
You got to pull off here
and turn around.

330
00:17:21.595 --> 00:17:24.053
No. I have to go to Brentwood
to get my kids at school.

331
00:17:25.345 --> 00:17:27.010
What do you mean?
I have to get through.

332
00:17:27.011 --> 00:17:28.511
They're about to start
evacuating the schools

333
00:17:28.512 --> 00:17:30.219
- in Brentwood anyway.
- Well. if they're evacuating

334
00:17:30.220 --> 00:17:32.094
the schools. then I really
need to get through

335
00:17:32.095 --> 00:17:34.219
so I can. you know.
evacuate my children.

336
00:17:34.220 --> 00:17:35.636
Ma'am. I can't let you through.

337
00:17:35.637 --> 00:17:37.177
Dude. what the fuck
is your problem?

338
00:17:37.178 --> 00:17:38.928
- Helen.
- My kids are over there.

339
00:17:38.929 --> 00:17:40.719
- Helen. Helen. this is...
- I have to go get them.

340
00:17:40.720 --> 00:17:41.803
This isn't helping.
Come on.

341
00:17:41.804 --> 00:17:43.719
We'll figure something else out.

342
00:17:43.720 --> 00:17:45.844
I'm sorry. okay? I am.

343
00:17:45.845 --> 00:17:47.929
Let's just go.

344
00:17:52.470 --> 00:17:54.512
Can you call Trevor?

345
00:18:01.637 --> 00:18:03.595
Voice mail.

346
00:18:07.470 --> 00:18:10.177
- Fuck. Stacey. too.
- What?

347
00:18:10.178 --> 00:18:12.594
Do we know anyone on the
Westside who could pick 'em up?

348
00:18:12.595 --> 00:18:14.969
Um...

349
00:18:14.970 --> 00:18:15.928
Yeah.

350
00:18:15.929 --> 00:18:17.804
Uh. Brooklyn's mom.

351
00:18:20.512 --> 00:18:22.303
Good idea.

352
00:18:24.470 --> 00:18:26.010
Um. I'll pack a bag for the kids

353
00:18:26.011 --> 00:18:27.803
in case we can't
get back over here.

354
00:18:27.804 --> 00:18:29.803
Can you call Whitney.
see what's up with her flight?

355
00:18:29.804 --> 00:18:31.679
Yeah. I'll check in
with Martin. too.

356
00:18:33.512 --> 00:18:34.594
Priya.

357
00:18:34.595 --> 00:18:36.427
Oh. hi.

358
00:18:36.428 --> 00:18:39.844
Isn't he the most beautiful
baby you've ever seen?

359
00:18:39.845 --> 00:18:43.010
Yeah... he is beautiful. yeah.
Where's Sierra?

360
00:18:43.011 --> 00:18:45.719
Sierra is packing.

361
00:18:45.720 --> 00:18:47.594
- Hi.
- Hello?

362
00:18:47.595 --> 00:18:49.344
- Hi.
- Um. sorry.

363
00:18:49.345 --> 00:18:51.427
Uh. it was starting
to smell like smoke up here.

364
00:18:51.428 --> 00:18:53.302
I wanted to get Eddie
out of the hills.

365
00:18:53.303 --> 00:18:54.844
I didn't want
to bother you guys.

366
00:18:54.845 --> 00:18:57.052
'cause you seemed kind of busy.
so I called Priya.

367
00:18:57.053 --> 00:18:59.636
- Oh.
- They're going to stay

368
00:18:59.637 --> 00:19:02.302
with Abdul and me
until the smoke clears.

369
00:19:02.303 --> 00:19:04.469
For as long as they like.

370
00:19:04.470 --> 00:19:06.595
The boy should get to know
his grandparents.

371
00:19:08.345 --> 00:19:09.969
Thank you.

372
00:19:09.970 --> 00:19:11.594
Mm-hmm.
I'll wait outside.

373
00:19:11.595 --> 00:19:13.970
Okay. Be safe.

374
00:19:26.553 --> 00:19:27.845
What's wrong?

375
00:19:29.261 --> 00:19:33.427
Uh. they're changing
the name of my movie.

376
00:19:33.428 --> 00:19:35.302
Who is?

377
00:19:35.303 --> 00:19:37.511
The producers of Descent.
They're...

378
00:19:37.512 --> 00:19:39.552
They're changing the title
to something else.

379
00:19:39.553 --> 00:19:42.302
and they're offering me a buyout
to take my name off the credits.

380
00:19:42.303 --> 00:19:45.470
So... they're erasing me
from my own story.

381
00:19:56.220 --> 00:19:58.053
I'm sorry.

382
00:20:06.220 --> 00:20:07.761
It's Lauren.

383
00:20:07.762 --> 00:20:09.679
Hey. Lauren. what's...

384
00:20:11.136 --> 00:20:12.553
What do you mean?

385
00:20:14.553 --> 00:20:17.469
Well. where did they go?
I... Yeah.

386
00:20:17.470 --> 00:20:19.594
Okay. I gotta...
Yeah. Of course.

387
00:20:19.595 --> 00:20:21.094
Uh. bye.

388
00:20:21.095 --> 00:20:23.761
Um. Trevor and Stacey
weren't at school.

389
00:20:23.762 --> 00:20:25.135
What? Where are they?

390
00:20:25.136 --> 00:20:26.803
I don't know. Brooklyn said
someone else picked them up.

391
00:20:26.804 --> 00:20:28.469
but he doesn't know who.

392
00:20:28.470 --> 00:20:30.220
Okay. I'll call Trevor.
you call Stacey.

393
00:20:36.470 --> 00:20:38.511
- It's just a voice mail.
- It's just ringing.

394
00:20:38.512 --> 00:20:40.678
I don't understand.
Where would they go?

395
00:20:40.679 --> 00:20:43.010
- The school wouldn't have let them just go.
- Well. they're teenagers.

396
00:20:43.011 --> 00:20:44.761
They can go
when they want to go.

397
00:20:44.762 --> 00:20:47.260
I don't... I don't un...
I mean. no one's texted me.

398
00:20:47.261 --> 00:20:48.719
Anyone else who could
have picked them up?

399
00:20:48.720 --> 00:20:50.302
I don't know.
I mean. I-I-I don't...

400
00:20:50.303 --> 00:20:53.010
I have this. um...
the-the tracking app thingy.

401
00:20:53.011 --> 00:20:54.969
I don't... Can you do that?

402
00:20:54.970 --> 00:20:56.844
- Let me see.
- I've never used it.

403
00:20:56.845 --> 00:20:59.387
- Okay. it's finding Trevor.
- Okay.

404
00:21:00.595 --> 00:21:02.177
That's weird.

405
00:21:02.178 --> 00:21:03.970
- What is?
- Why is he in Malibu?

406
00:21:07.053 --> 00:21:09.136
- Oh. my God.
- What?

407
00:21:11.136 --> 00:21:13.969
They're at Sasha's.

408
00:21:13.970 --> 00:21:15.845
I mean. what the fuck?

409
00:21:19.720 --> 00:21:21.804
Hi. Do you have my kids?

410
00:21:24.470 --> 00:21:27.511
No. I don't want to FaceTime.
I don't want to FaceTime.

411
00:21:27.512 --> 00:21:31.636
Hey. hey. I just want you
to see that your kids are fine.

412
00:21:31.637 --> 00:21:33.135
They're happy. safe.

413
00:21:33.136 --> 00:21:34.761
Look. Hey. kids.
say hi to your mother.

414
00:21:34.762 --> 00:21:36.094
Hi. guys.

415
00:21:36.095 --> 00:21:37.803
- Look. Sasha.
- Yes?

416
00:21:37.804 --> 00:21:40.511
You cannot just get my
fucking kids without telling me.

417
00:21:40.512 --> 00:21:42.386
I tried calling you.

418
00:21:42.387 --> 00:21:44.219
but your phone kept going
straight to voice mail.

419
00:21:44.220 --> 00:21:45.886
Listen. the city's gridlocked.

420
00:21:45.887 --> 00:21:47.427
and-and I'm sending over
a helicopter.

421
00:21:47.428 --> 00:21:48.678
You're sending
a helicopter where?

422
00:21:48.679 --> 00:21:50.427
To get you.

423
00:21:50.428 --> 00:21:52.052
Yeah. I've-I've checked it
with my security guys.

424
00:21:52.053 --> 00:21:53.469
There's a landing pad
just up the...

425
00:21:53.470 --> 00:21:54.844
the hill from your house.

426
00:21:54.845 --> 00:21:56.302
Yeah. I can't...
I can't do that.

427
00:21:56.303 --> 00:21:57.928
I have a house full of people.

428
00:21:57.929 --> 00:21:59.219
Of course you do.

429
00:21:59.220 --> 00:22:01.094
What else is new?
So. who's there?

430
00:22:01.095 --> 00:22:02.761
Perhaps we can
squeeze them in. too.

431
00:22:02.762 --> 00:22:03.762
Go. Be with the kids.

432
00:22:05.220 --> 00:22:07.386
- Is that Noah?
- Yes!

433
00:22:07.387 --> 00:22:08.552
What the fuck is he doing there?

434
00:22:08.553 --> 00:22:10.511
Helen. have you...
have you watched the news?

435
00:22:10.512 --> 00:22:12.177
Have you seen what
he's being accused of?

436
00:22:12.178 --> 00:22:14.552
Yeah. that's why
he's here. Sasha.

437
00:22:14.553 --> 00:22:17.094
so we can figure out
how to deal with our children.

438
00:22:17.095 --> 00:22:19.260
I just told you.
your kids are fine.

439
00:22:19.261 --> 00:22:20.803
Okay? They're doing great.

440
00:22:20.804 --> 00:22:22.094
But if you rather want
to stay there

441
00:22:22.095 --> 00:22:23.844
and help your ex-husband

442
00:22:23.845 --> 00:22:25.636
deal with the fact
that he's just made a fool

443
00:22:25.637 --> 00:22:27.386
of your whole family.
that's your choice.

444
00:22:27.387 --> 00:22:29.052
The helicopter will be there
in 20 minutes.

445
00:22:29.053 --> 00:22:30.637
I suggest you get on it.

446
00:22:33.178 --> 00:22:35.303
You should go.

447
00:22:39.011 --> 00:22:40.511
What about you?

448
00:22:40.512 --> 00:22:43.302
I'll be okay.
I'm gonna keep trying Whitney.

449
00:22:43.303 --> 00:22:45.427
Maybe I'll just go
to the airport and wait.

450
00:22:45.428 --> 00:22:47.969
I've got her
flight number somewhere.

451
00:22:47.970 --> 00:22:50.679
I think I should talk to her
in person when she lands.

452
00:22:53.345 --> 00:22:55.387
She probably has
a lot of questions.

453
00:22:59.095 --> 00:23:01.052
Thank you.

454
00:23:01.053 --> 00:23:03.260
For what?

455
00:23:03.261 --> 00:23:05.469
For this morning. today.

456
00:23:05.470 --> 00:23:07.929
All I did was yell at you.

457
00:23:14.011 --> 00:23:15.679
You're such
a great mother. Helen.

458
00:23:20.178 --> 00:23:22.969
We've got four
great kids. and...

459
00:23:22.970 --> 00:23:24.929
I know it's not because of me.

460
00:23:27.053 --> 00:23:29.178
I'm very grateful.

461
00:24:10.804 --> 00:24:13.094
There are several
major fires blanketing

462
00:24:13.095 --> 00:24:15.552
the stretch between
Westwood and Ventura County.

463
00:24:15.553 --> 00:24:17.344
Helicopters are still
trying to get

464
00:24:17.345 --> 00:24:20.678
these wildfires under control
and they continue to drop

465
00:24:20.679 --> 00:24:24.427
gallons of water and retardant
onto the fires. Uh...

466
00:24:24.428 --> 00:24:26.636
Hey. guys. You okay?

467
00:24:26.637 --> 00:24:28.386
We're fine.

468
00:24:28.387 --> 00:24:30.719
Trevor. let me see.
What happened? Trevor.

469
00:24:30.720 --> 00:24:34.010
Apparently. Brooklyn said
some shit about Dad.

470
00:24:34.011 --> 00:24:35.970
Trevor hit him.
and he hit Trevor back.

471
00:24:37.011 --> 00:24:38.844
Honey. I'm so sorry.

472
00:24:38.845 --> 00:24:41.135
Yeah. well. it's not your fault
Dad fucks everything up.

473
00:24:41.136 --> 00:24:42.928
Who's hungry?

474
00:24:42.929 --> 00:24:44.761
Hey. Helen. you made it.

475
00:24:44.762 --> 00:24:46.010
- Hey.
- Great.

476
00:24:46.011 --> 00:24:49.177
- Trevor. can you take this?
- Yeah.

477
00:24:49.178 --> 00:24:51.136
- Talk to you for a second?
- Sure.

478
00:24:54.720 --> 00:24:57.135
Listen... I'm really sorry

479
00:24:57.136 --> 00:25:00.844
that I just went
and got your kids like that.

480
00:25:00.845 --> 00:25:03.636
But the truth is that
Trevor called me and told me

481
00:25:03.637 --> 00:25:05.427
that Noah was at your house

482
00:25:05.428 --> 00:25:07.135
and that he didn't want
to see him.

483
00:25:07.136 --> 00:25:11.094
So he asked me to come
and get him and Stacey.

484
00:25:11.095 --> 00:25:12.761
Really?

485
00:25:12.762 --> 00:25:16.552
Yeah. And I didn't want
to tell you over the phone.

486
00:25:16.553 --> 00:25:18.761
And I'm also sorry
about last night.

487
00:25:18.762 --> 00:25:21.512
I-I-I was exhausted. and...

488
00:25:23.720 --> 00:25:26.719
Listen. I... I love you.

489
00:25:26.720 --> 00:25:29.094
But sometimes it frightens me
how big your world is.

490
00:25:29.095 --> 00:25:32.219
And it's not you
who should change; it's me.

491
00:25:32.220 --> 00:25:35.427
And-and... and that is why
I-I-I did what I did

492
00:25:35.428 --> 00:25:37.678
and went and got your kids.
'cause that is exactly

493
00:25:37.679 --> 00:25:39.553
the sort of thing
that you would have done.

494
00:25:44.220 --> 00:25:46.053
Well. I'm sorry. too.

495
00:25:47.929 --> 00:25:49.553
Yeah. okay.

496
00:25:51.428 --> 00:25:53.552
- Glass of wine?
- Yeah. please.

497
00:25:53.553 --> 00:25:55.469
All right.

498
00:25:55.470 --> 00:25:57.594
Audrey Nelson
is one of the women

499
00:25:57.595 --> 00:25:59.094
accusing Solloway.

500
00:25:59.095 --> 00:26:00.844
We caught up with her
this morning

501
00:26:00.845 --> 00:26:03.803
at the annual
Women in Media Breakfast.

502
00:26:03.804 --> 00:26:06.052
Yes. I was in
his creative writing seminar

503
00:26:06.053 --> 00:26:08.052
my sophomore year at Livingston.

504
00:26:08.053 --> 00:26:09.427
Do you have a comment

505
00:26:09.428 --> 00:26:12.135
about the very damning article
that came out this morning

506
00:26:12.136 --> 00:26:13.552
concerning his behavior
toward women?

507
00:26:13.553 --> 00:26:15.886
All I will say is that

508
00:26:15.887 --> 00:26:17.344
it's always terrifying

509
00:26:17.345 --> 00:26:19.302
to speak out
against powerful men.

510
00:26:19.303 --> 00:26:22.010
especially if you have
